On the uposatha day, they enjoin their disciples thus: ‘Come, good man, having laid aside all clothes, recite: ‘I am not anywhere the belonging of anyone, nor is there anywhere anything in any place that is mine.’
However, his parents know: ‘This is our son.’
And he knows: ‘These are my parents.’
His wife and children know: ‘He is our supporter.’
And he knows: ‘These are my wife and children.’
His slaves, workers, and servants know: ‘He is our master.’
And he knows: ‘These are my slaves, workers, and servants.’
Thus on an occasion when they should be enjoined in truthfulness, enjoin them in false speech.
On these five grounds a bhikkhu is suspected and distrusted as ‘an evil bhikkhu’ though he be of unshakable character.”
