We will overcome loss … fame … disrepute … honor … lack of honor … evil desires … bad friendship whenever it arises.’
It is in such a way that you should train yourselves.” 
We will patiently endure cold and heat, hunger and thirst; contact with flies, mosquitoes, wind, the burning sun, and serpents; rude and offensive ways of speech; we will bear up with arisen bodily feelings that are painful, racking, sharp, piercing, harrowing, disagreeable, sapping one’s vitality.’
It is in this way, bhikkhus, that you should train yourselves.”
