Which is better, for a strong man to force open one’s mouth with a hot iron spike—burning, blazing, and glowing—and insert a hot copper ball—burning, blazing, and glowing—which burns one’s lips, mouth, tongue, throat, and stomach, and comes out from below taking along one’s entrails, or for one to consume almsfood given out of faith by affluent khattiyas, brahmins, or householders?”
